@startuml
' Color conversion relationship diagram for xer

title xer color conversion relationships

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Monospaced
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  BorderColor #444444
  RoundCorner 8
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5F5F5
  BorderColor #777777
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #AA0055
  Thickness 1
}
left to right direction

rectangle "basic_rgb<T>\nrgb" as RGB
rectangle "basic_cmy<T>\ncmy" as CMY
rectangle "basic_hsv<T>\nhsv" as HSV
rectangle "basic_gray<T>\ngray" as GRAY
rectangle "basic_xyz<T>\nxyz\nCIE 1931 XYZ" as XYZ
rectangle "basic_lab<T>\nlab\nCIE 1976 L*a*b*" as LAB
rectangle "basic_luv<T>\nluv\nCIE 1976 L*u*v*" as LUV

note top of RGB
Public name is rgb,
but RGB <-> XYZ assumes
sRGB with the D65 white point.
end note

note bottom of GRAY
RGB -> gray has practical variants:
- to_luma_gray
- to_luminance_gray
- to_gray
end note

RGB <--> CMY : to_cmy / to_rgb
RGB <--> HSV : to_hsv / to_rgb
RGB --> GRAY : to_luma_gray\n/to_luminance_gray\n/to_gray
GRAY --> RGB : to_rgb
RGB <--> XYZ : to_xyz / to_rgb
XYZ <--> LAB : to_lab / to_xyz
XYZ <--> LUV : to_luv / to_xyz

legend bottom
|= Space |= Role |
| RGB | Normalized display-oriented RGB values |
| CMY | Complementary subtractive representation |
| HSV | Hue-saturation-value representation |
| Gray | Display-oriented grayscale value |
| XYZ | Colorimetric hub for Lab and Luv |
| Lab | Perceptual color space based on XYZ |
| Luv | Perceptual color space based on XYZ |
endlegend

@enduml
